import seaborn as sns
import statsmodels.api as sm
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='ignore')
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    sns.lineplot(x='year', y='pop', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the trend of population over time?', wrap=True)
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
```

import seaborn as sns
import statsmodels.api as sm
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='ignore')
    ax = sns.boxplot(x='country', y='life_expect', data=data)
    ax.set_xticklabels(ax.get_xticklabels(), rotation=90)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.title('How does life expectancy vary across different countries?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
```

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))

    ax = sns.barplot(x='cluster', y='pop', data=data, ci=None)

    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
